Troll Thane of the 14th Hammer <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6B8E23><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ugharadin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gharadin</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#5F9EA0>(11/26/01 9:30:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=755.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Midgard server</span><hr size=1> My armorcrafter on test is only around 250, but I have zero problem switching to a real server. That's a very good point about there not being much chance for RvR on test. If I had to vote, I'd say Guinevere just because I think a lot of us made low-level characters there when the game first came out, but I don't have any characters high enough to mind starting somewhere else if that's what everyone wants. One thing to keep in mind is Guinevere is a roleplaying server in case that bothers anyone. On the other hand, I think it's a bit less crowded than other servers.<br>
